Interface PSOEventListener


  • public interface PSOEventListener
    Event listener interface for integration with other software modules such as GUI

    • Method Detail

      • searchStarted

        void searchStarted()
        Notifies the listener that the algorithm execution has started

      • searchUpdate

        void searchUpdate(int iteration,
                  double avg,
                  double min,
                  double max,
                  double best)
        Updates the listener with the information about current search progress (currently after each 50th iteration).
        Parameters:
        iteration - current iteration
        avg - average evaluation for all particles in the swarm
        min - best evaluation in the current swarm
        max - worst evaluation in the current swarm
        best - best solution found so far

      • foundNewBest

        void foundNewBest(double evaluation)
        Notifies the listener that an improvement in the search has been done and that the new best so far with the evaluation evaluation has been found.
        Parameters:
        evaluation - new best evaluation

      • searchFinished

        void searchFinished(Results results,
                    WordSet wordSet)
        Notifies the listener that the search progress has finished. This can be due to an optimal solution (evaluation = 0) being found, reaching the maximum allowed number of iterations or reaching the maximum allowed execution time, whichever of those conditions happens first.
        Parameters:
        results - search results
        wordSet - training set
